\begin_body

\begin_layout Title
Structured copula modelling of insurance liabilities
\end_layout

\begin_layout Author
Piet de Jong 
\newline

\newline
 
\size small
Department of Actuarial Studies, 
\newline
 Macquarie University, NSW 2109, Australia.
 
\newline
 Email: piet.dejong@mq.edu.au
\end_layout

\begin_layout Date

\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
This article employs copulas to model total claims losses arising from different
 lines of insurance.
 There are two contributions.
 First a flexible method is developed to generate copulas.
 Second total losses are considered given the marginal distributions are
 Weibull.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
Keywords:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Copulas
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Introduction
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This article develops and discusses a practical, structural way of generating
 copulas.
 By structural we mean the copula is generated from a generating mechanism
 typical of statistical modeling.
 This contrasts with the usual way of specifying copulas directly via functional
 forms as discussed for example in 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

