}
\end_layout

\end_inset

, if 
\begin_inset Formula $\rho\approx0$
\end_inset

 then 
\begin_inset Formula $\ln(\rho)$
\end_inset

 is very negative and 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{1t}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{2t}$
\end_inset

 are virtually unrelated since 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{2t}$
\end_inset

 is dominated by 
\begin_inset Formula $\ln(\rho)\eps_{t}$
\end_inset

.
 If 
\begin_inset Formula $\rho\approx1$
\end_inset

 then 
\begin_inset Formula $\ln(\rho)\approx0$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{1t}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{2t}$
\end_inset

 are highly dependent.
 The panels in 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Standard


\backslash
fref{
\end_layout

\end_inset

fig1
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Standard

}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 suggest increasing upper tail dependence in that the conditional probability
 
\begin_inset Formula $P(\check{s}_{2t}>u|\check{s}_{1t}>u)$
\end_inset

 increases as 
\begin_inset Formula $u\rightarrow1$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The chi--squared specification for 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha_{t}$
\end_inset

 can be changed to other extreme value or heavy tailed distributions.
 For example the log--normal is an alternative.
 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Standard


\backslash
fref{
\end_layout

\end_inset

fig2
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Standard

}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 illustrates the copula when 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha_{t}\sim t_{1}$
\end_inset

, in (
\begin_inset LatexCommand \ref{chi1}

\end_inset

), a 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

t" random variable with 1 degree of freedom.
 In this case tail dependence appears to increases in both tails.
 Thus when 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha_{t}$
\end_inset

 is near zero, the effect of 
\begin_inset Formula $\eps_{t}$
\end_inset

 is to mask the dependence while if 
\begin_inset Formula $|\alpha_{t}|$
\end_inset

 is large the dependence increases: the perturbing effect of 
\begin_inset Formula $\eps_{t}$
\end_inset

 in these cases is negligible.
\end_layout

