\begin_inset Formula $\check{y}_{t}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\check{s}_{t}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
One way to check whether the distribution of the 
\begin_inset Formula $\check{s}_{t}$
\end_inset

 is similar to that of the 
\begin_inset Formula $\check{y}_{t}$
\end_inset

 is to divide the unit hypercube into smaller volumes or cells indexed by
 
\begin_inset Formula $c$
\end_inset

 and count the number of 
\begin_inset Formula $\check{y}_{t}$
\end_inset

 in each cell.
 These are then compared to the expected number 
\begin_inset Formula $e_{c}$
\end_inset

 calculated for given 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\rho$
\end_inset

