\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 distribution.
 Thus 
\begin_inset Formula $(x_{\alpha},0)$
\end_inset

 is in the set of 
\begin_inset Formula $x+y\ge s_{\alpha}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
we wish to determine 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{\alpha}$
\end_inset

 say such that In two dimensions this defines a line, in three dimensions
